SINGER Nomcebo Zikode believes the support they are getting for the song Jerusalema is a direct blessing from God. The song has since become a global phenomenon through the #JerusalemaChallenge. Nomcebo told Daily Sun that God is doing wonders with their music as she never expected the song to be so big. “I would love to thank God more than anything. I believe he brought me and Master KG together to do this song. ALSO READ:KHAYA DLADLA GETS ENGAGED “He knew South Africans could have a song that would dominate the world,” she said. She also thanked everyone who supported the song. Nomcebo also thanked the Minister of Sports, Arts and Culture Nathi Mthethwa for acknowledging their work. She said she released her album Xola Moya Wam, a month ago and people are loving it. She advised other artists to be patient. “It is important to love your craft. I know this is not an easy journey. People see you as a celebrity, but they don’t know where you come from. “I love my fans and I have not changed. Fame will not change Nomcebo,” she said.